Etymology.—
The new species name comes from the languages of the Dupaningan Agta, Itawes, and Ibanag of NE Luzon, an adjective meaning “large” in all three languages (see Tharp and Natividad 1976; 
Greenhill et al. 2008
; 
Robinson 2011
); we use it as an adjective in the nominative singular neuter.
